{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Ninety-nine percent of us have the dream of listeners."},{"time":4000,"text":"Not being the musicians -- the listeners, right?"},{"time":6000,"text":"And we crave one thing,"},{"time":8000,"text":"even though we kind of don't know it all the time."},{"time":10000,"text":"We crave to be in the room with the musician"},{"time":15000,"text":"the day it was recorded, the day it was played."},{"time":17000,"text":"And we go to live concerts, and we get that as much as we can."},{"time":20000,"text":"But then we listen to the other 99 percent of our stuff recorded."},{"time":23000,"text":"And it turns out the further back you go in history,"},{"time":26000,"text":"the little rougher it sounds."},{"time":28000,"text":"And so we said, there's a solution to this."},{"time":32000,"text":"Let's separate the performance, as a thing,"},{"time":36000,"text":"out from the recording, which was how it was made."},{"time":39000,"text":"You know, the thing with microphones in the room and all that day."},{"time":42000,"text":"But the performance itself was how the musicians worked their fingers,"},{"time":45000,"text":"and what instruments they were using."},{"time":47000,"text":"And it's the data hidden inside the recording."},{"time":52000,"text":"In order to do this, it's a lot of hardware and software"},{"time":55000,"text":"that runs in a very high resolution."},{"time":57000,"text":"And Yamaha makes an incredible thing called the Disklavier Pro"},{"time":61000,"text":"that looks like a nice grand piano there."},{"time":63000,"text":"And you probably didn't realize it's going to do all these things --"},{"time":65000,"text":"but full of solenoids, and fiber optics, and computers"},{"time":68000,"text":"and all this kind of stuff. The highest resolution out of Japan."},{"time":71000,"text":"And this just didn't work until we could cross this line that says high-definition."},{"time":75000,"text":"And we were able to cross this line, called the uncanny valley,"},{"time":78000,"text":"in terms of -- artificial intelligence terms."},{"time":83000,"text":"We have a process where we, you know,"},{"time":85000,"text":"kind of put it into the computer and digitize it, and then a whole lot of analysis."},{"time":88000,"text":"And we look at every single note,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and all the attributes of those notes:"},{"time":92000,"text":"how hard they were struck, and how they were held down,"},{"time":94000,"text":"and how you move the fingers."},{"time":96000,"text":"So we had to develop a whole new science of how you move your fingers."},{"time":98000,"text":"And, you know, it's a thing your piano teacher teaches you,"},{"time":101000,"text":"but we never had a science behind these kinds of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"I'm going to start with Glenn Gould."},{"time":106000,"text":"He died 25 years ago this year, and was born 75 years ago this year."},{"time":110000,"text":"Was a beloved pianist, maybe the great cult pianist of the twentieth century."},{"time":114000,"text":"He just got tired of being in front of an audience,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and felt like -- a performing monkey was, in fact, his term."},{"time":118000,"text":"So he stepped back, and did nothing but the crafting of his work."},{"time":122000,"text":"And Gould's specialty was playing Bach."},{"time":124000,"text":"His maybe most famous recording"},{"time":126000,"text":"was something called \"The Goldberg Variations.\""},{"time":128000,"text":"Bach only wrote themes and variations one time."},{"time":131000,"text":"He wrote some early pieces,"},{"time":133000,"text":"but late in his life, in his mature period,"},{"time":135000,"text":"he said, \"Here's a theme -- 30 variations.\""},{"time":138000,"text":"In fact, the theme isn't even the melody, it's the bass line."},{"time":141000,"text":"And Gould recorded it in two major recordings that you may know about,"},{"time":146000,"text":"one in mono, and one in stereo."},{"time":148000,"text":"And the one in mono, by the way, he used the pedal,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and as he got older, he said, \"No, no, wait a minute."},{"time":154000,"text":"I'm going to get very scientific about this, and not use the pedal.\""},{"time":157000,"text":"What I'd like you to hear live is the 1955 version,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and we'll play the first couple pieces of it."},{"time":163000,"text":"Glenn Gould, 1955."},{"time":166000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":319000,"text":"How about that?"},{"time":321000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"So let me tell you a little bit how this was done."},{"time":327000,"text":"First of all, let me get you to the end step."},{"time":329000,"text":"This is -- we have a fairly complex process"},{"time":331000,"text":"that, you know, software and musicians and so on,"},{"time":334000,"text":"but when we're all done, we know that the ear is the final arbiter."},{"time":339000,"text":"We can play the original in one ear, and a new recording in the other."},{"time":342000,"text":"So I'm going to do this for you right now, what you just heard."},{"time":345000,"text":"And in the right speaker is going to be the original recording,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and the left speaker is going to be the new recording,"},{"time":350000,"text":"actually of an instrument just like that one,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and I'm going to play them together at the same time."},{"time":355000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":361000,"text":"That's the original. [Unclear] That's the two together."},{"time":363000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"Before \"Jurassic Park,\""},{"time":401000,"text":"there was no science for how skin hung off of muscle, right?"},{"time":407000,"text":"So, in the video world,"},{"time":408000,"text":"we've been able to invent, in our lifetimes, natural behavior."},{"time":411000,"text":"And this is kind of another example"},{"time":413000,"text":"of putting a science behind natural behavior."},{"time":416000,"text":"And then you heard the original."},{"time":418000,"text":"Ultimately, I started with the experience."},{"time":420000,"text":"And the experience is: I want to be in the room and hear the musicians."},{"time":424000,"text":"Lots of you can afford to buy one of these."},{"time":426000,"text":"But, if not, there is now high-definition surround sound."},{"time":432000,"text":"And I got to tell you, if you haven't heard high-definition surround,"},{"time":435000,"text":"go down to your audio dealer, your audiophile dealer."},{"time":437000,"text":"It's so involving compared to regular stereo."},{"time":441000,"text":"But if you don't have that, maybe you can listen on your headphones."},{"time":443000,"text":"And so on the same disk we have five recordings --"},{"time":445000,"text":"Sony has five recordings."},{"time":447000,"text":"And you could listen in headphones"},{"time":449000,"text":"with this thing called binaural recording."},{"time":452000,"text":"And it's a dummy head that sits in front of the instrument,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and it's got microphones where the ears are."},{"time":460000,"text":"And when you put on headphones, and you listen to this,"},{"time":462000,"text":"you're inside of Glenn Gould's body."},{"time":464000,"text":"And it is a chuckle until, you know, the musicians,"},{"time":467000,"text":"who are musicians who play the piano, listen to this, say,"},{"time":469000,"text":"\"I can't believe it! It's just what it's like to play the piano.\""},{"time":471000,"text":"Except now you're inside Glenn Gould's body playing the piano,"},{"time":473000,"text":"and it feels like your fingers are making the decisions"},{"time":475000,"text":"and moving through the whole process."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's a game changer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"Here's now something we know in spectacular quality."},{"time":481000,"text":"The whole process is very sensitive to temperature and humidity."},{"time":485000,"text":"What you heard today was not perfect."},{"time":487000,"text":"It's an amalgam of wood, and cast iron, and felt,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and steel strings, and all these,"},{"time":493000,"text":"and they're all amazingly sensitive to temperature and humidity."},{"time":496000,"text":"So when you go into the recording session,"},{"time":499000,"text":"you get to stop after every piece and rebuild the piano if you need to."},{"time":503000,"text":"There's the whole action there, sitting, kind of, on the side,"},{"time":505000,"text":"and the dummy head and our recording engineers"},{"time":507000,"text":"standing around while we rebuild the piano."},{"time":509000,"text":"Without putting dates next to these things,"},{"time":511000,"text":"step-by-step music will be turned into data,"},{"time":514000,"text":"like every field that's occurred in the past 35 or 40 years."},{"time":518000,"text":"Audio has come very late to this game --"},{"time":521000,"text":"I'm not talking about digitizing, and bits, and re-mastering."},{"time":524000,"text":"I'm talking about turn it into the data that it was made from,"},{"time":527000,"text":"which is how it was performed."},{"time":529000,"text":"And audio came very late because our ears are so hard to fool --"},{"time":532000,"text":"they're high-resolution, and they're wired straight to our emotions,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and you can't trick them very easily."},{"time":537000,"text":"Your eyes are pretty happy with some color and movement, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"All right, there's this episode of \"Star Trek.\""},{"time":543000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":546000,"text":"I get it -- it was all just laid in for me yesterday there."},{"time":548000,"text":"The episode of \"Star Trek\" for me was James Daly played Methuselah --"},{"time":552000,"text":"remember this one?"},{"time":554000,"text":"And at some point he's dancing with his --"},{"time":557000,"text":"and I won't ruin the episode for you, from 1967."},{"time":559000,"text":"Right, do you know where I'm going?"},{"time":561000,"text":"And Nimoy, I'm sorry, Spock sits down at the piano,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and he starts playing this Brahms waltz, and they all dance to it."},{"time":567000,"text":"And then Spock turns round, he goes,"},{"time":569000,"text":"\"James, I know all of the Brahms waltzes,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and I don't believe this is one of them in the category.\""},{"time":578000,"text":"That's where I'm at."},{"time":580000,"text":"I want to hear the waltzes Brahms didn't write."},{"time":584000,"text":"I want to hear the pieces that Horowitz didn't play."},{"time":588000,"text":"But I believe we're on a path now, when we get to data,"},{"time":593000,"text":"that we can distill styles, and templates, and formulas, and all these kinds of things,"},{"time":597000,"text":"again, that you've seen happen in the computer graphics world."},{"time":600000,"text":"It's now coming in this world."},{"time":602000,"text":"The transition will be this one."},{"time":604000,"text":"It says right now, we think music is notes and how they're played."},{"time":607000,"text":"And I believe this is coming."},{"time":609000,"text":"Because what you've just heard was a computer playing data --"},{"time":614000,"text":"no Glenn Gould in the room."},{"time":616000,"text":"But yet, it was human."},{"time":618000,"text":"And I believe you'll get to the next step, the real dream of listeners."},{"time":621000,"text":"Every time you listen to a recording today,"},{"time":624000,"text":"every time you take out your iPod and whatever,"},{"time":626000,"text":"every time you listen to it, it's the same thing -- it's frozen."},{"time":631000,"text":"Wouldn't it be cool if every time you listened, it could be different?"},{"time":635000,"text":"This morning, you're sadder, you want to hear your song,"},{"time":638000,"text":"the same song, played sadder than you did yesterday."},{"time":640000,"text":"You want to hear it played by different musicians."},{"time":642000,"text":"You want to hear it in different rooms and whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"We've seen all these \"Star Treks,\" and they're all holodeck episodes as well."},{"time":647000,"text":"Every time I listen to that, I get goose bumps."},{"time":650000,"text":"It's so amazing, it's so exciting."},{"time":653000,"text":"Every time I listen to that recording it's like, \"Oh my God,"},{"time":655000,"text":"I can't believe I'm in the same room. I can't believe this is happening.\""},{"time":657000,"text":"It's a way better experience"},{"time":659000,"text":"than whatever you're used to listening to, in whatever form."},{"time":661000,"text":"And lastly, I will wrap up with one minute of Art Tatum."},{"time":666000,"text":"So I've really overshot my budget here."},{"time":668000,"text":"We made a new recording of him"},{"time":671000,"text":"playing in the Shrine Auditorium in September."},{"time":674000,"text":"It was a concert he recorded in the Shrine Auditorium in 1949."},{"time":678000,"text":"And I've got to tell you, we have this lab"},{"time":680000,"text":"where we build and measure everything, back in Raleigh, North Carolina,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and we flew out to Los Angeles."},{"time":686000,"text":"And as the president of the company,"},{"time":688000,"text":"I didn't feel real comfortable about where we were."},{"time":691000,"text":"That's a real uncomfortable feeling,"},{"time":693000,"text":"when all the equipment's come out and a whole Sony team,"},{"time":695000,"text":"and people are going to be sitting there in the audience."},{"time":697000,"text":"And we put the piano on the sweet spot of the stage in the Shrine,"},{"time":701000,"text":"which has not changed since 1949, still seats 6,000 people."},{"time":705000,"text":"And on the sweet spot on the stage, Tatum starts playing ..."},{"time":708000,"text":"and every note, every beat, every slur, every accent, every pedal"},{"time":714000,"text":"was perfect, because he played it for that room on that day."},{"time":718000,"text":"And we captured all that data all over again."},{"time":720000,"text":"And I want you to hear that right now."},{"time":722000,"text":"And fortunately, it's right in here."},{"time":724000,"text":"This is an encore he used to do."},{"time":727000,"text":"It's one minute long."},{"time":729000,"text":"It's an Irish jig, and I want you to hear his humor."},{"time":731000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":787000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":788000,"text":"And that's just what the live audience did."},{"time":791000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":793000,"text":"So thank you very much, Michael, thank you for the opportunity."}]}]}